 The ageing of the population has also contributed to rising costs, though not as much as for pensions.
 The most important of these is demography.
 Only halfway through the 21st century will the number of over-65s peak, at about 190m.
 The impact of an ageing population on healthcare costs is less clear-cut.
 But that would also have deleterious effects, according to the OECD.
